The paper deals with the study of a graph class, which is a generalization of threshold graphs and unit interval graphs. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also presents a vertex ordering characterization and a linear-time recognition algorithm for the class, which indicates that it may belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) or Graph Theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the study of clique paths, which is a topic commonly studied in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.GT, and cs.LG, in that order.
